# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
.pytest_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.ty_cache/

# mise
# (mise.lock IS committed — reproducible tool installs)

# graphify-out: graph.json is DERIVED — regenerable from committed inputs
# (sources/*.manifest + sources/extractions/) via `mise run kb-build` (free, no
# LLM). Per CLAUDE.md invariant 3 and graphify's design, it is GITIGNORED: at
# aggregate scale it exceeds git/GitHub limits (119MB > 100MB), and consumers
# query via the MCP server (`mise run kb-serve`) or a pushed graph DB
# (neo4j/falkordb), never a git blob. manifest.json (change-detection) and
# .graphify_labels.json (labels keyed to NON-deterministic Louvain community ids
# — not reproducible across rebuilds, so they can't "ship together") are likewise
# derived/coupled and gitignored. COMMITTED = reproducible inputs + authored
# graphify-out/memory/ (work-memory). Other views regenerate via `kb-artifacts`.
graphify-out/graph.json
graphify-out/manifest.json
graphify-out/cache/
graphify-out/transcripts/
graphify-out/converted/
graphify-out/*.html
graphify-out/*.svg
graphify-out/*.graphml
graphify-out/cypher.txt
graphify-out/wiki/
graphify-out/obsidian/
graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md
graphify-out/.graphify_*
# committed under graphify-out/: ONLY memory/ (authored work-memory).
# graph.json / manifest.json / .graphify_* (labels, learning overlay) are derived.

# graphify per-install state (generated by `graphify install`/runs; not source)
.claude/skills/graphify/.graphify_version
.claude/skills/**/.graphify_root

# External REPOS — cloned on demand from sources/*.manifest at a pinned SHA, NEVER
# committed. Non-repo sources (video transcripts, docs, PDFs) that CAN'T be
# deterministically re-fetched ARE vendored under sources/media/.
sources/*/
!sources/extractions/
!sources/media/
!sources/.gitkeep
sources/media/*.m4a       # audio — the transcript is the committed artifact
sources/media/*.pdf.txt   # regenerable from the committed .pdf via pypdf

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
# reflect derived doc (regenerable via `graphify reflect`); memory/ IS tracked (authored)
graphify-out/reflections/
# graphify dated backup dirs (redundant with git history)
graphify-out/20[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]-[0-9][0-9]/
